# Badar Trader CRM — environment variable NAMES (no values)
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# IMPORTANT: The live app does NOT read most of these from a .env file.
# Runtime configuration is stored in the `settings` table (key/value) in
# Supabase and read at request time by the edge functions. This file exists
# only to document which secrets/config the system expects, for whoever takes
# the project over. Do NOT commit real values here.
#
# Where each is actually used:
#   - Edge functions receive SUPABASE_URL + SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY as
#     Supabase-provided function secrets.
#   - WhatsApp + Meta credentials live in `settings` (wa_access_token,
#     wa_phone_number_id, meta_token, meta_account_id, gh_push_token, ...).
#     whatsapp-webhook also checks WHATSAPP_* env vars first, then falls back
#     to the settings table.
#   - The static frontend (index.html / js/config.js) uses only the public
#     SUPABASE_URL + SUPABASE_ANON_KEY.

# --- Supabase ---
SUPABASE_URL=
SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=
SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY=

# --- WhatsApp Cloud API ---
WHATSAPP_ACCESS_TOKEN=
WHATSAPP_PHONE_NUMBER_ID=
WHATSAPP_VERIFY_TOKEN=

# --- Meta / Facebook (ads + WABA) ---
META_ACCESS_TOKEN=
META_AD_ACCOUNT_ID=
META_WABA_ID=
META_PIXEL_ID=

# --- GitHub (repo-writer tooling only) ---
GH_PUSH_TOKEN=
